The forces of the giant strike are gathering
The League Unions and the National Federation of Workers&#39; Commissions will establish a strike commission on Friday to coordinate Monday&#39;s strike that will last indefinitely.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday - the day on which the final vote on the public health law will be held - the work stoppage will begin.
This action will certainly cause great difficulties in transport, since the railway traffic will be completely stopped and until 1:00 p.m. the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will also be on strike.
On Friday afternoon, the League Unions will report on the details of their strike on Monday that they will hold jointly with the National Federation of Workers&#39; Commissions.
Likewise, the strike commission of the LIGA and the National Union of Machinists will be constituted, which will coordinate the actions on Monday.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday the participating unions will go on strike indefinitely, if an agreement is not reached with the government.
This means that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the public health law - they did not report the date of the end of the strike.
If the National Assembly disapproves of the public health law, the unions will immediately withdraw their call to strike.
Instead, if the law is passed, the strike committees will meet and decide on the future.
Based on the Monday National Assembly agenda, it is also possible that the public health law will only be voted on late at night, or perhaps around midnight.
