Some unions announced their strike for an indefinite period, others for a defined period.
Until Thursday afternoon, the State Railroad and the Free Union of Railroad Workers (SLTF) could not reach an agreement even on the minimum services, although, as the Christmas holidays approach, more and more people are they travel on trains.
According to information received so far, from the beginning of the day until 1:00 p.m. the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will be on strike, those of Budapest Airport from 7 to 9 in the morning, they will hold a four-hour strike the LIGA Unions of the Electrical and Thermal Energy Industry, the Educators Unions called for a strike of 2 and the Democratic Union of Educators from 2 to 8 hours.
The Hungarian Medical Association will strike a national strike at alternate hours and the Democratic Union of Workers in the Health and Social Sector (SDTSSS), which is part of the Trade Union Cooperation Forum, will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands made by the League is that the government withdraw its proposal regarding public health reform and submit a new conception to a social debate.
The second demand is that they gradually introduce the new way of calculating pensions that will come into effect next year.
The third is that they ensure, even before 2010, in the case of advanced pensions, the possibility that deserving occupations can enter the system.
The fourth reason for the strike is that the Free Union of Railroad Workers (SLTF), which is part of the League Unions, does not accept the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport on the railway lateral lines and awaits a different proposal.
