Congress approves the transposition of the Mifid, which entered into force 1 November
Parallel to its parliamentary process, which ended today with the vote by Congress of the amendments incorporated to the bill in the Senate, the Government has submitted to a public hearing the regulations that will develop the new law, with the objective that both enter into force before the year is out.
The representatives of the different groups agreed to highlight the effort made by deputies and senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulations in order to guarantee the protection of investors and to regulate in detail the activity of the entities so that the markets function efficiently.
The Mifid, which modifies the Securities Market Law, involves the modernization of financial markets, while reinforcing investor protection, improving the supervisory powers of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and fostering cooperation between the different supervisors in the European Union.
The new regulations will allow the provision of financial advisory services to both specialized firms and individuals or legal entities and creates a new type of financial services firms (ESIS), financial advisory firms (AFI), which join securities firms. , securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it expands the number of systems for executing operations on financial instruments, so that the regulated secondary markets are joined by multilateral trading systems and order internalization systems, which will compete with current stock managers.
The Law also obliges investment services companies to disclose in the market information on the key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and forms of risk management and requires them to keep a record of all the operations they carry out, in order to facilitate supervision by the CNMV.
During its passage through the Economic Commission of Congress, several modifications were incorporated, among which it stands out that the securitized debts are considered as a &quot;complex&quot; financial instrument given their high danger for the investor, which has been demonstrated with what happened with the US subprime mortgage debt.
In addition, the transposition of the directive was used to legally delimit the functions that economics and business graduates can perform 30 years after the royal decree that delimits the professional functions reserved for economists was approved in 1977.
For its part, the Senate incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as the mediator, who will work for someone else, will not require authorization from the CNMV and will be able to provide its services for marketing products and attracting customers to different investment firms at the same time.
